The paper discusses a methodology for designing efficient deep neural network systems using virtual models, which involves hardware and software components. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Computer Science related to Architecture (cs.AR), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Emerging Technologies (cs.ET), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Among these, cs.AR and cs.SY are the most likely categories as they deal with hardware and system-level design, which are the main focus of the paper. However, cs.ET, cs.LG, and cs.CV are also possible categories as they are related to emerging technologies, machine learning, and computer vision, respectively, which are all relevant to the paper's topic.
